description: Pexip Holding ASA, a video technology company, provides end-to-end video conferencing platform and digital infrastructure in the Americas, Europe, the Middle East, Africa, and the Asia Pacific. It offers self-hosted software application and as-a-service deployment options for enterprise video conferencing, built on its proprietary Infinity technology. The company also offers Pexip Connect Standard, which provides interoperability between traditional meeting room devices like Cisco, HP/Poly, and Avaya; Pexip Connect Essentials, a solution that connects traditional meeting room devices; Pexip Connect for Teams Rooms, a solution that lets users join any meeting, or place and receive calls to and from anyone, complete with a native experience from their teams rooms devices; Pexip Connect for Zoom Rooms, a solution that lets users join teams meeting and enjoy a native experience; and Pexip Connect for Government through FedRAMP and StateRAMP. In addition, it provides Pexip Secure Meetings for Defense, a unified communication for defense sector; Pexip Secure Meetings for Government, a solution for communication for government officials, agencies, and citizens; Pexip Secure Meetings for Justice, a secure and private communication solution for court system; Pexip Secure Meetings for Health, a solution with video visits for healthcare providers and patients; Pexip Private AI platforme, which enables AI-powered live captions and translations in secure video meetings; and Pexip Secure Scheduler for Web that offers flexible and secure scheduling of virtual meetings. Further, the company offers Pexip Video Platform Self-Hosted, a customizable and secure video platform for complete control and flexibility; Pexip Video Platform as a Service, an easy-to-use video engine solution for regulated industries; and trust centers, as well as provides professional, room management, and training services. Pexip Holding ASA was founded in 2011 and is headquartered in Oslo, Norway.
